  • All Classes Interface Summary Enum Summary 
    Class Description
    BetType
    Provided enum type for Further Programming representing a type of Bet
    See inline comments for where you need to provide additional code
    Color
    Provided enum type for Further Programming representing the color of a Slot on the Gaming Wheel NOTE: GREEN0 and GREEN00 are provided as dfferent colors to differentiate the 0 and 00 which are both numeric zero in our implementation
    GameEngine
    Assignment interface for Further Programming providing main model functionality for this Roulette style game
    GameEngineCallback
    Assignment interface for Further Programming to notify client of GameEngine events
    i.e.
    Player
    Assignment interface for Further Programming representing the player to be implemented by SimplePlayer class with the following constructor: public SimplePlayer(String playerId, String playerName, int initialPoints) NOTE: playerID is unique and if another player with same id is added it replaces the previous player
    Slot
    Assignment interface for Further Programming representing a colored/numbered Slot on the Gaming Wheel (setting values is handled by the implementing class constructor(s)) IMPORTANT: To facilitate testing, your implementation of this class should be model.SlotImpl i.e.
